    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That sounds like a good start. I think some of my students might get confused tho, because they'll hear some people saying that substantive due process is just a way for judges to make up new laws that aren't actually in the Constitution. How should I address those criticisms in the lesson?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
